OL,6,FWhen police arrived at their home,
OL,7,FMatthews was taken to the Royal Stoke
OL,8,FHospital, where he commented that
OL,9,Ftheir sleep had been disturbed and "I
OL,10,Fdecided we had had enough".
OL,12,FHe also told police and nurses that
OL,13,FMrs Matthews told him: "No Peter,
OL,14,Fdon't do this" and that he wanted to
OL,15,Fdie "as punishment" for what he had
OL,16,Fdone.
OL,18,FMr Mason said: "He said the killing
OL,19,Fwas not planned and accepted that
OL,20,FCarol had not wanted him to do it.
